Cyber threats have affected our democratic process.
And there is a growing trend.
The more advanced computer technology, the more vulnerable the means we use to protect data.
In particular, a new computer technology, called a quantum computer, uses microscopic particles of nature to dramatically increase the computing power of computers.
It's computationally powerful enough to crack many of the encryption systems we use today.
So are we hopeless?
Should we start packing up our electronic survival gear for the coming data apocalypse?
