For me, this is a very exciting time in the history of secure communications.
About 15 years ago, I learned that we've unlocked new skills to create quantum effects that don't exist in nature. I was very excited.
The idea of using the fundamental laws of physics to advance cryptography is exciting to me.
Today, a select group of companies and labs, including mine, are advancing this technology to the stage of practical application.
That's right.
We're going to fight quantum with quantum.
How to achieve it?
First, let's take a quick look at the world of encryption.
You need a briefcase, and you have some important documents to give to your good friend, James Bond, to be locked up and safe.
