Cybercriminals use reverse engineering to create the pseudo-random number generator behind the turntable.
That way they have a good chance of predicting the turn of the wheel and making a lot of money.
The secret key is also insecure.
Having a true random number generator is important for generating secure passwords.
For years, researchers have been trying to create a true random number generator.
